Argentine private equity firm
Southern Cross Group acquired a 78 percent stake in shipbuilder
and river boat operator  Ultrapetrol Ltd (ULTR) , Clarin reported today,
without saying how it got the information.  The firm owned by Argentine businessman Norberto Morita
paid $220 million for the stake, the Buenos Aires-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
